properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 11 at 7:51PM PST until January 13 at 12:00AM PST by NWS Portland OR
properties.description:
* WHAT...West wind 15 to 25 kt with gusts to 30 kt through
tonight, becoming west to northwest 25 to 35 kt with gusts to 40
kt Sunday. Combined seas subsiding to 18 to 22 ft at 13 seconds
tonight. Seas will build back to around 22 to 25 ft at 13
seconds on Sunday.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Cape Shoalwater WA to Florence OR
out 60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 8 AM PST Sunday.
For the Gale Warning, from 8 AM to midnight PST Sunday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM PST SUNDAY... ...GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM SUNDAY TO MIDNIGHT PST SUNDAY NIGHT
